Protein Name : IgE Fc in complex with a neutralizing antibody
Organism : Homo sapiens
PDB ID : 5ANM
Experimental method : X-Ray Diffraction
Resolution : 2.85 Å

Biological Significance : Immunoglobulin E (IgE) antibodies are human antibibodies.
They play a critical role in mediating allergic reactions.
They are known for their powerful effector functions activated through binding to Fc receptors FcεRI and FcεRII/CD23. 
